The '''Randoni''' were [[Human/Legends|Humans]] native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Randon/Legends|Randon]],<ref name="The Essential Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> known as merchants and traders . One could distinguish Randoni merchants from others by their rough-woven garb and loose hairstyle. [[Gender/Legends|Female]] ward-cousins were greatly highly honored due to their potential inheritance. It is also likely that the Randoni were the origin of [[Randoni Yellow Plague]], a drink.

Early in their spacefaring history, the first Randoni merchants and traders would deposit their treasures in hidden vaults. In [[22 ABY/Legends|22 ABY]], [[Tionne Solusar]] came across an ancient song which told about that event and where the treasures were hidden. A Randoni trader was so interested that in exchange for the song, he gave her a [[Jemlaat-class in-system sail yacht|''Jemlaat''-class yacht]] named ''[[Lore Seeker]]''.

